The paper discusses the design and testing of a Deep Learning architecture for automated medical prognosis, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing, leading to the possibility of cs.CL (Computation and Language) being a relevant sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges and pitfalls of designing Deep Learning architectures for medical prognosis, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
